CHANGELOG
=========

This file follows Keep a Changelog (https://keepachangelog.com/) and
SemVer with the relaxation declared in docs/PLAN.md §12 decision 12:
v0.x is unstable; v1.0.0 freezes the public API.

## Unreleased

### Changed

- `nwrfc.Conn.Lock` and `nwrfc.Conn.Unlock` were removed from the public API.
  Callers must stop managing `Conn` locking directly: serialization of RFC
  calls, metadata operations, resets, session close, and connection close is
  now internal to the package. Use `Pool` for concurrent RFC work instead of
  sharing one connection across goroutines.

## v0.2.0 — 2026-05-08 (nexus-spec integration hardening)

The v0.2.0 cycle is the production-readiness pass for the
nexus-spec downstream consumer. It hardens the public nwrfc
API for first-class Windows VDI deployment (Citrix, VMware
Horizon, AWS WorkSpaces, AVD), introduces refined error and
redaction taxonomies, and locks the cancellation contract.

The roadmap that drove this release is
docs/ROADMAP_NEXUS_INTEGRATION.md. Every item below has an
entry in that document with acceptance criteria.

### Minimum SDK supported

- SAP NetWeaver RFC SDK 7.50 PL3+. PL18 is the verified
  reference. WebSocket RFC requires PL10+; bgRFC requires
  PL5+. See docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md.

### Breaking changes vs v0.1.x

- `Conn.Reset()` now takes a `context.Context` parameter
  (`Conn.Reset(ctx)`). The old zero-arg form is removed.
  Callers using `pool.Do` or `AfterAcquire` already pass a
  ctx — update the inner `c.Reset()` call to `c.Reset(ctx)`.
- `backend.Backend.Reset` interface signature also adds the
  ctx parameter; this affects `nwrfcmock` and any
  out-of-tree backend implementation. The change is
  necessary for the unified cancel-watcher contract: every
  blocking op honors ctx through the same path.
- `LogonError` is now sometimes a `*PasswordExpiredError` /
  `*UserLockedError` / `*InvalidCredentialsError` /
  `*UnknownLogonFailureError` (subtypes embedding
  LogonError). Generic callers using
  `errors.Is(err, ErrLogon)` or
  `errors.As(err, &le *LogonError)` keep working unchanged.
  Callers that branched on the concrete `*LogonError` type
  alone now lose specificity to the subtypes — switch to
  `errors.As` against the subtype, or stay on `errors.Is`
  against `ErrLogon`.

### Added

- `Conn.Cancel() error` — public mid-call cancel. Idempotent,
  goroutine-safe, calls `RfcCancel` via the new
  `backend.Cancellable` capability. Documented SAP caveat for
  mutating BAPIs (`outcome unknown`).
  Evidence: docs/EVIDENCE/sdk-cancel.md.
- Logon error subtypes:
  - `*PasswordExpiredError` + `ErrPasswordExpired`
  - `*UserLockedError` + `ErrUserLocked`
  - `*InvalidCredentialsError` + `ErrInvalidCredentials`
  - `*UnknownLogonFailureError` + `ErrUnknownLogonFailure`
  Classification table is the single source of truth in
  `nwrfc/errors_logon.go`.
- Public type aliases `nwrfc.Date`, `nwrfc.Time`,
  `nwrfc.UTCLong`, `nwrfc.Decimal`. Callers no longer need
  to import `internal/backend` for ABAP scalar struct
  fields. Convenience function `nwrfc.AsTime(d, t)`.
- `Params.MaxTraceLevel int` — process-global trace cap with
  tightest-wins semantics. `SetTraceLevel(n)` with `n` above
  the installed cap returns `*ConfigError` referencing
  docs/SECURITY.md §5.
- `PoolConfig.AlwaysReset bool` — when true, the pool calls
  `Conn.Reset` on every checkout BEFORE `AfterAcquire`. A
  failed Reset surfaces to the Acquire caller; the pool does
  not loop.
- `nwrfc.Params` implements `fmt.Stringer` and `fmt.GoStringer`
  with the same redaction policy as `LogValue`. Accidental
  `fmt.Println(p)` no longer leaks credentials.
- Hardlock for `Params.WSHost` against
  `Capabilities.WebSocketRFC`: an Open with WSHost set on a
  PL that does not support WebSocket RFC fails fast with
  `*UnsupportedFeatureError`. No silent transport downgrade.
- `EnsureSDK`, `SDKVersion`, `Capabilities` now memoized via
  `sync.OnceValue`. Repeated calls are zero-cost.
- New shared cgo cancel watcher (`internal/sdkbackend/cancel.go`)
  — Open, Ping, Reset, Describe, Invoke, InvokeInTransaction,
  InvokeInUnit all go through one helper. Eliminates the
  duplicated goroutine pattern previously inlined in five
  files.

### Changed

- `internal/backend/types.go::SensitiveKeys` extended with
  `snc_sso`. New `SensitivePrefixes` and `SensitiveSuffixes`
  catch families like `passwd_*`, `*_token`, `*_secret`,
  `*_key`, `bearer*`, `saml*`, `x509*`, `snc*`,
  `mysapsso*`. Single source of truth via `IsSensitiveKey`.
- `nwrfcotel` and `nwrfc/errors.go` consult `IsSensitiveKey`
  rather than carrying their own match tables.
- The legacy `gorfc/gorfc.go` file no longer hardcodes
  `C:/Tools/nwrfcsdk` paths. Operators set `CGO_CFLAGS` /
  `CGO_LDFLAGS` via `SAPNWRFC_HOME` (matches the
  `internal/sdkbackend/cgo_directives.go` pattern).
- Logon errors emitted from the cgo backend route through
  `buildLogonError` so `errors.Is(err, ErrLogon)` and the
  new subtype sentinels both work.

### Documentation

- `docs/ROADMAP_NEXUS_INTEGRATION.md` (NEW) — the living
  roadmap that drives this release.
- `docs/DEPLOY.md` (NEW) — VDI deployment playbook covering
  Linux RHEL/Ubuntu LTS, Windows Server 2019+, Windows 10/11
  Enterprise, Citrix, VMware Horizon, AWS WorkSpaces, AVD.
  Documents `$ORIGIN`-relative rpath, Windows DLL
  co-location, and the anti-patterns to avoid.
- `docs/EVIDENCE/SCHEMA.md` (NEW) — mandatory schema for
  Categoria-B (live SAP) integration test evidence.
- `docs/EVIDENCE/sdk-cancel.md` (NEW) — RfcCancel symbol
  presence and thread-safety evidence for the §3 decision in
  the roadmap.
- `docs/BUILD.md` — added IDE / gopls configuration for
  developers without local SDK headers.
- `CONTRIBUTING.md` — added the maintainer signed-tag
  release procedure.
- `docs/ERRORS.md` — TBD to be updated with the logon
  subtypes and the cancellation caveat (tracked under the
  v0.2.0 follow-up doc-sync).

### CI

- `.github/workflows/ci.yml` (NEW) — Linux nosdk + Windows
  nosdk + Linux→Windows zig cross-compile + manual SDK-real
  matrix. Aggregator job for required-status check.

### Security

- All v0.2.0 changes preserve the AGENTS.md non-negotiables:
  no SDK redistribution, no credential leakage in logs, no
  silent fallback when a capability is missing or an SDK
  call fails.

## Unreleased — 2026-05-07 (tRFC/qRFC/bgRFC client wiring + qRFC correction)

Implements the cgo bindings and Go-side dispatch for the
transactional client APIs that earlier rounds had stubbed out.
Also corrects a documentation error from the link-validation
round about how qRFC routing actually works.

### Corrected

The "Phantom symbols" finding in docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md
about `RfcSetQueueName` was right (the symbol truly does NOT
exist in PL18) but the proposed fix was wrong. The earlier note
claimed qRFC routing is done via `RfcCreateUnit`'s queue list.
Re-reading sapnwrfc.h §2120 with the SDK in hand:

- `RfcCreateTransaction(handle, tid, queueName, info)` is the
  tRFC AND qRFC creator: queueName=NULL means tRFC, non-NULL
  means qRFC. There is no separate qRFC creator.
- `RfcCreateUnit(handle, uid, queueNames[], count, ...)` is the
  bgRFC creator, a different API entirely.

The Conn.NewQueuedTransaction path is therefore implementable
over RfcCreateTransaction itself; we did not need to rewrite
over RfcCreateUnit.

### Added — bindings

- internal/sdkbackend/transaction.go: cgo bindings for
  `RfcCreateTransaction` (tRFC and qRFC, depending on
  queueName), `RfcInvokeInTransaction`,
  `RfcSubmitTransaction`, `RfcConfirmTransaction`,
  `RfcDestroyTransaction`. Includes a per-package txnRegistry
  that maps opaque uint64 handles to RFC_TRANSACTION_HANDLE
  pointers, mirroring the connRegistry pattern so cgo
  unsafe.Pointer never leaks across the public boundary.
- internal/sdkbackend/unit.go: cgo bindings for `RfcCreateUnit`
  (synchronous type 'T' when queues is empty; queued type 'Q'
  with the listed queues otherwise), `RfcInvokeInUnit`,
  `RfcSubmitUnit`, `RfcConfirmUnit` (takes RFC_UNIT_IDENTIFIER
  not the handle, per sapnwrfc.h §2331), `RfcDestroyUnit`,
  `RfcGetUnitState`. Includes a unitRegistry and a
  goUnitIdentifierToC helper that copies a 32-char Go UnitID
  into the embedded SAP_UC[33] array of the C identifier
  struct.
- internal/backend/backend.go: new optional capability
  interfaces `TransactionalBackend` (5 methods) and
  `BgRFCBackend` (6 methods), plus `TxHandle`, `UnitHandle`,
  `UnitIdentifier`, and `UnitState` types that cross the
  boundary without leaking cgo pointers.

### Refactored

- nwrfc/transactional.go: replaced the previous stub
  `*UnsupportedFeatureError` returns with type-asserted
  dispatch to the new backend interfaces. The Transaction
  struct now carries a `backend.TxHandle`; Unit carries a
  `backend.UnitHandle` plus the SDK-populated
  `backend.UnitIdentifier` (so callers do not need to track
  the (type 'T'|'Q') byte separately for Confirm/State).
- nwrfc.UnitState constants now alias the backend.UnitState
  values verbatim instead of redefining them, with an
  enum-equality test (TestUnitState_EnumValuesMatchBackend) to
  keep them locked.
- Added Transaction.Destroy and Unit.Destroy as explicit
  release paths for cases where Submit was never attempted
  (validation failed Go-side after Create succeeded). Both
  are idempotent.

### Added — behavior tests

nwrfc/transactional_sdk_test.go (gated by `cgo &&
!nwrfc_nosdk`):

- TestSDKBackend_SatisfiesTransactionalInterface — compile-time
  check would catch this; the runtime assertion is a clearer
  failure mode for future contributors who refactor the
  backend.
- TestSDKBackend_SatisfiesBgRFCInterface — same for bgRFC.
- TestNewTID_ShapeContract / TestNewUnitID_ShapeContract — 24
  and 32 uppercase hex chars respectively, per ABAP contract.
- TestNewTID_Uniqueness — 1000 generations, all distinct.
- TestUnitState_EnumValuesMatchBackend — public-API constants
  match backend-package values byte-for-byte.
- TestNewQueuedTransaction_FailsClosed — error path on a
  closed/nil Conn surfaces a real error rather than panicking.

The full Submit/Confirm round-trip against `SM58` / `SMQ1` /
`SBGRFCMON` is the live-system gate (Categoria B per the
earlier "SDK link-validation pass" entry below) and remains
pending.

### Documentation

- docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md: rewrote the "Transactional (T3)"
  section with the actual SDK function-by-function bindings
  and the Go file each lives in. Corrected the
  "Phantom symbols" entry for RfcSetQueueName to reflect that
  qRFC routing is via RfcCreateTransaction's queueName, not
  RfcCreateUnit's queue list.

## Unreleased — 2026-05-07 (SDK behavior-validation pass)

Builds on the same-day link-validation pass. With the SDK linkable,
this pass exercises SDK calls that are observable purely from the
loaded library — no SAP system needed — and surfaces real bugs the
link-only pass could not see.

### Added — `internal/sdktest/` package

A dedicated test-only package (`internal/sdktest/`) hosts cgo-using
behavior probes that exercise the SAP NetWeaver RFC SDK directly,
independent of the production binding. Required because Go's tooling
refuses to build cgo inside test files of a cgo-using package
(internal/sdkbackend uses cgo for the production binding, so its
test files cannot `import "C"`; see golang/go#27091). The package's
production code (`sdkprobe.go`) calls the SDK; its `*_test.go` files
are pure Go and consume those probes.

### Added — bindings that were declared but not implemented

- `internal/sdkbackend/trace.go`: SetTraceLevel / SetTraceDir /
  setTraceEncoding wrap RfcSetTraceLevel / RfcSetTraceDir /
  RfcSetTraceEncoding (sapnwrfc.h §812-§946). The public `nwrfc`
  package's SetTrace* helpers existed since T1.13 but type-asserted
  on a `backend.Trace` interface that no implementation satisfied;
  every call returned `*UnsupportedFeatureError` even with the SDK
  linked. The cgo backend now satisfies the interface end-to-end.
- `internal/sdkbackend/lang.go`: LanguageISOToSAP / LanguageSAPToISO
  wrap RfcLanguageIsoToSap / RfcLanguageSapToIso. Same gap as
  trace — the public API existed; the cgo binding did not.
- `internal/sdkbackend/ini.go`: SetIniPath / ReloadIniFile wrap
  RfcSetIniPath / RfcReloadIniFile. Same gap.

### Fixed — bugs surfaced by the new behavior tests

- `internal/sdkbackend/version.go`: RfcGetVersion returns its
  release line packed into the `major` out-param as a 4-digit
  decimal (PL18 reports `7500/0/18`). The previous code published
  Major=7500 directly, which made every `Version.AtLeast(7, x, y)`
  return true regardless of x/y, silently turning every capability
  check to a yes — including Throughput on PL18 (which actually
  needs PL53+). The fix decomposes 7500 → Major=7, Minor=50.
  Capabilities.Throughput on PL18 now correctly reports `false`.
- `internal/sdkbackend/lang.go`: RfcLanguageIsoToSap writes ONLY
  the result code unit and does NOT null-terminate. The first
  draft used mallocU (which does not zero memory), so the result
  decoded as e.g. `"Eᷬ"` (real "E" + a stale UTF-16 code unit
  from prior heap content). Fix: memset the entire output buffer
  to zero before the SDK call. Same for LanguageSAPToISO.
- Inline constants table in earlier draft of `internal/sdktest/
  sdkprobe.go` had `RfcTypeInt8 = 25` and `RfcTypeUtcLong = 30`,
  both wrong. The SDK header (sapnwrfc.h §93-§113) places these
  at 31 and 32 respectively (continuing the implicit enum from
  XSTRING=30). The string-table test caught it as a duplicate
  ("RFCTYPE_NULL").

### Added — behavior tests

Public API (`nwrfc/sdk_behavior_test.go`):

- TestSDKVersion_NotZero — pins Major/Minor on a real SDK; would
  have caught the version-decomposition bug.
- TestCapabilities_DerivedFromVersion — sanity: UTCLong always
  true on 7.50+.
- TestLanguageISOToSAP_KnownLanguages — round-trip for EN, DE,
  PT, FR, ES, JA, ZH (note: ZH is the SAP code "1", not "Z").
- TestLanguageSAPToISO_RoundTrip — symmetric inverse.
- TestLanguageISOToSAP_RejectsBadInput — Go-side validation.
- TestSetTraceLevel_RangeCheck — wrapper rejects level<0 or >3
  before the SDK silently accepts and discards.
- TestSetTraceDir_RealFile — sets trace dir to a temp dir, raises
  trace level, observes that `dev_rfc.log` + `rfc*.trc` actually
  land in our temp dir.

Probe package (`internal/sdktest/sdkprobe_test.go`):

- TestSDKEncoder_RoundTripVsUCS2 — 18 hard strings (Latin
  diacritics, Cyrillic, Greek, Hebrew RTL, Arabic RTL, Devanagari,
  Kanji BMP, Kana, Hangul, supplementary-plane emoji, supplementary
  kanji 𠮷 U+20BB7, mathematical bold digits 𝟘…𝟛, mixed CJK).
  For each: encode via SDK → assert SAP_UC bytes are byte-identical
  to the pure-Go ucs2.EncodeNullTerminated reference → decode back
  via SDK → assert exact UTF-8 round-trip. All pass on PL18.
- TestSDKEncoder_LongString — 1 MiB of mixed-script repeated
  text; catches off-by-one in buffer sizing.
- TestSDKEncoder_NoLeak — 100,000 encode+decode+free cycles;
  Go-side HeapAlloc grows by ~13.8 KB total, well under the
  1 MiB slack. Provides behavioral evidence for the
  helpers.c "mallocU pairs with standard free()" contract.
- TestRcAsString_KnownCodes — 6 RFC_RC values yield 6 distinct
  non-empty strings.
- TestTypeAsString_KnownTypes — 18 RFCTYPE values yield 14
  distinct strings (some types share a stringification, e.g.
  RFCTYPE_DECF16/34 may map to similar text — not pinned).
- TestDirectionAsString_KnownDirections — 4 RFC_DIRECTION
  values yield 4 distinct strings.

### Documentation

- docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md: rows for the functions exercised by
  the new tests now carry `✅ behavior verified PL18` (stronger
  than the link-only `✅ (PL18)` from the previous round).
- This entry replaces the former "Unreleased — SDK link-validation
  pass" entry; the link round and the behavior round share the
  same date and stay separated by paragraph for traceability.

## Original Unreleased entry — 2026-05-07 (SDK link-validation pass)

First end-to-end build of the cgo backend against an installed SAP
NetWeaver RFC SDK (7.50 PL18, Linux x86_64, build 637). The previous
v1.0.0 surface was specified and unit-tested without the SDK in
hand. This pass linked `internal/sdkbackend` against the real
`libsapnwrfc.so` for the first time.

### Fixed (cgo backend regressions surfaced by the link step)

- internal/sdkbackend: helpers `goMallocU` / `goFreeU` /
  `goStrlenU` / `goSetParamActive` were defined as `static`
  functions inside the cgo preamble of `cgo_directives.go`, which
  made them invisible to the cgo preambles of sibling files (each
  Go file with `import "C"` carries its own preamble). Extracted
  to `internal/sdkbackend/helpers.{c,h}` so they have package-wide
  linkage. Each cgo `.go` file now does `#include "helpers.h"`.
  AGENTS.md §Engineering Rules: explicit malloc/free pairing kept
  grep-able in one file.
- internal/sdkbackend/helpers.c: `goFreeU` now calls the standard
  `free()`. The SDK's `<sapucrfc.h>` defines `mallocU` as a macro
  that expands to `mallocU16(len)` → `(SAP_UTF16*) malloc(len *
  sizeof(SAP_UTF16))`. There is **no** matching `freeU` macro in
  the public header set; the previous binding referenced one. The
  legacy `gorfc/gorfc.go` had this right (see its 224-227 comment
  block). Documented in `docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md`.
- internal/sdkbackend/conn.go: `attr.type_` → `attr._type`. cgo
  prefixes (not suffixes) Go-keyword field names with `_`, so the
  C field `type` becomes `_type` on the Go side. The bug was a
  typo against cgo's renaming rule; sibling code in
  `internal/sdkbackend/{fill,wrap}.go` already used `pd._type`
  correctly.
- internal/sdkbackend/fill.go: `fillFunctionParameter` was passing
  a `C.RFC_FUNCTION_HANDLE` directly to `fillVariable`, whose
  signature expects `unsafe.Pointer`. cgo represents `void*`
  typedefs as opaque pointer types that don't implicitly convert
  to `unsafe.Pointer`; added the explicit `unsafe.Pointer(fh)`
  conversion (matching `wrap.go:46`).

### Test hardening (separate SDK-free from SAP-backed)

- gorfc/gorfc_test.go: every integration test now calls
  `gorfcTestEnvOrSkip(t)` at entry. The helper existed but was
  not invoked, so without `GORFC_TEST_USER` set the tests would
  panic on a nil `*Connection`. Per AGENTS.md §Engineering Rules:
  "Tests must separate SDK-free unit tests from SAP-backed
  integration tests."
- nwrfc/conn_nosdk_test.go (new) + nwrfc/conn_test.go: moved
  `TestOpen_NoSDK_SurfacesAsSDKUnavailable` behind a
  `//go:build !cgo || nwrfc_nosdk` tag. The test asserts that
  the no-SDK stub backend surfaces `*SDKUnavailableError`, which
  is the wrong assertion when the cgo+SDK backend is actually
  wired in.

### Documentation (SDK reality)

- docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md: flipped 🟡 → ✅ for symbols whose
  existence is now confirmed by `nm -D libsapnwrfc.so` against
  PL18: `RfcCancel`, `RfcSetParameterActive`, `RfcSetIniPath`,
  `RfcReloadIniFile`, `RfcLoadCryptoLibrary`,
  `RfcLanguageIsoToSap` / `RfcLanguageSapToIso`,
  `RfcIsConnectionHandleValid`, `RfcGetTypeLength`,
  `RfcAddFunctionDesc` / `RfcRemoveFunctionDesc`, the throughput
  family (7.53+), the tRFC family, the bgRFC family, the server
  install handlers (`RfcInstallTransactionHandlers`,
  `RfcInstallBgRfcHandlers`,
  `RfcInstall{Generic,}ServerFunction`), and `RfcRegisterServer`
  / `RfcShutdownServer` / `RfcListenAndDispatch`.
- docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md "Phantom symbols" section: two
  symbols previously documented in PLAN.md drafts do **not**
  exist in PL18 (`nm -D` confirmed):
  - `RfcStartOrResumeServer` — the real SDK symbol is
    `RfcStartServer` (sapnwrfc.h:1441). Server accept loops use
    `RfcListenAndDispatch`.
  - `RfcSetQueueName` — qRFC routing in NW RFC SDK 7.50 is done
    by passing the queue list to `RfcCreateUnit`, not via a
    separate setter.
  Per AGENTS.md non-negotiables ("Do not introduce silent
  fallback behavior"), these are now flagged 🔴 in the map.
- nwrfc/transactional.go: comment in `Transaction.Submit`
  updated to reflect the qRFC reality (queue routing via
  `RfcCreateUnit`, not `RfcSetQueueName`).

### Pending — Categoria B (live SAP system)

The following gates remain blocked on a reachable SAP test system
with classic RFC enabled:

- STFC_CONNECTION + STFC_STRUCTURE round-trip
- `RfcCancel` actual cancel-mid-call timing
- tRFC `Submit` / `Confirm` against `SM58`
- bgRFC `Unit` lifecycle visible in `SBGRFCMON`
- `RfcInstallTransactionHandlers` / `RfcInstallBgRfcHandlers`
  trampoline (T3.4 cgo glue)
- qRFC reimplementation over `RfcCreateUnit`

Browser-only access (Fiori / S/4HANA Cloud Public) is **not**
sufficient for these — classic RFC needs the dispatcher port
(`32<sysnr>`) reachable, which Cloud Public Edition does not
expose. The SDK is in hand; the system is the gate.

## v1.0.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 4: Go-native differentiation, GA)

### Added — Tier 4

- nwrfcmock package (T4.1): pure-Go [backend.Backend]
  implementation. HandleFunc / SetDescriptor / SetVersion /
  SetCapabilities + CallCount / OpenCount / CloseCount
  counters. Routes nwrfc.Call through user-registered handlers
  for hermetic unit tests; no cgo, no SAP system needed.
- cmd/nwrfc-gen (T4.2): codegen tool that produces typed Go
  client packages from a SAP function descriptor. Live mode
  connects to a SAP system; offline mode reads a JSON
  descriptor (suitable for vendoring schemas in source).
  Generated code is gofmt'd, has no runtime overhead beyond
  the marshal layer the core library already pays.
- nwrfcidoc package (T4.3): pure-Go IDoc parser/builder over
  the EDI_DC40 + EDI_DD40 wire layout. Encode / Decode the
  control record + segment table; suitable for
  IDOC_INBOUND_ASYNCHRONOUS payloads.
- cmd/nwrfc-bridge (T4.4): HTTP/JSON gateway. POST a JSON
  body to /rfc/<FN>; the bridge invokes the RFC and returns
  JSON. Pool-backed; per-error-category HTTP status mapping
  (logon → 401, abap → 400, timeout → 504, comm → 502).
  Designed as a sidecar; does NOT do auth (deploy behind a
  reverse proxy).
- docs/MIGRATION_FROM_GORFC.md (T4.5): mechanical port guide
  from upstream `github.com/sap/gorfc`. Side-by-side examples,
  behavioral-change call-outs (date/time policy, build tag,
  redaction, no-SDK mode, leak fix), Pool/Session/Server
  pointers.

### Stability

- Public API in nwrfc/, nwrfcparam/, nwrfcotel/, nwrfcmock/,
  nwrfcidoc/ is now frozen per docs/PLAN.md §12 decision 12.
  Breaking changes wait for v2.x.

### Out of scope

- 🟡 SAP server callbacks (T3.4 cgo trampoline) ship in a
  point release once a SAP sandbox with bgRFC config
  (SBGRFCCONF) is reachable for validation. The Go-side
  interface (TransactionHandlers / BgRFCHandlers /
  Server.Install*Handlers) is final.

## v0.3.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 3: advanced protocols and CLI)

### Added — Tier 3

- tRFC client (T3.1): `Conn.NewTransaction` returns a
  `Transaction` carrying a fresh `TID`. `Transaction.Call` /
  `Submit` / `Confirm` are the lifecycle. The cgo backend's
  Submit/Confirm bindings remain pending validation against
  a SAP sandbox; the Go-side API is final.
- qRFC client (T3.2): `Conn.NewQueuedTransaction(name)`.
  Same shape as tRFC plus a queue name routed via
  `RfcSetQueueName`.
- bgRFC client (T3.3): `Conn.NewUnit(queues...)`. Returns a
  `Unit` with `Call` / `Submit` / `Confirm` / `State`. Uses
  the SDK's `RfcCreate/Invoke/Submit/Confirm/GetState/
  DestroyUnit` family (capability-gated against SDK
  ≥ 7.50 PL5).
- tRFC/qRFC/bgRFC server handler interfaces (T3.4):
  `TransactionHandlers` (OnCheck/Commit/Rollback/Confirm) and
  `BgRFCHandlers` (adds OnGetState). Wired into
  `Server.InstallTransactionHandlers` /
  `InstallBgRFCHandlers`. The cgo trampoline is the
  follow-up; the Go-side API is final.
- Repository abstraction (T3.5): cross-Conn metadata cache.
  `NewRepository().Use(conn).Describe / Preload / Snapshot /
  Apply / Invalidate`. Snapshots are `map[string]
  backend.FunctionDescriptor`, suitable for serializing to
  disk and reloading. Pre-load reduces first-call latency.
- cmd/nwrfc CLI (T3.6): `ping`, `describe`, `call`, `version`
  subcommands. Uses GORFC_TEST_* env vars for connection
  parameters; useful for spot-checking SAP RFC connectivity
  and printing function descriptors as JSON.

## v0.2.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 2: observability + providers + sync server)

### Added — Tier 2

- nwrfcparam.BAPIReturn helper (T2.1): typed view of the
  BAPIRET2 ABAP DDIC structure. ParseBAPIReturn handles
  single map / slice / []any shapes the marshaling layer
  emits. AsError converts error-typed rows into
  `*nwrfc.ABAPApplicationError`. CheckRETURN(resp) is the
  one-liner for the conventional RETURN parameter.
- Throughput accumulator (T2.2): `nwrfc.NewThroughput` +
  `Attach(conn)` + `Stats()`. SDK-side counters via
  `RfcSetThroughputOnConnection` (SDK ≥ 7.53 🟡); Go-side
  fallback via Conn lifecycle hooks when SDK is too old.
- nwrfcotel subpackage (T2.3): RedactHandler is a
  slog.Handler wrapper that strips backend.SensitiveKeys
  attributes; recurses into slog.GroupValue. ConnListener +
  TracerListener emit per-event slog records / OTel spans.
  Tracer / Span minimal interface stays version-independent
  of go.opentelemetry.io/otel.
- DestinationProvider + ServerProvider (T2.4):
  control-plane resolution of destination + server
  registrations. SetDestinationProvider /
  SetServerProvider install process-wide resolvers.
  OpenDest now consults provider → IniFS → SDK in order.
- Custom IniFS (T2.5): `IniFS = io/fs.FS`. SetIniFS installs
  a process-wide source. parseIni handles `[DEST=NAME]`
  blocks, comments, KEY=VALUE pairs, with Extra escape
  hatch for unknown keys.
- Metadata cache (T2.6): Conn.Describe goes through the SDK
  cache; InvalidateMetadata wraps RfcRemoveFunctionDesc.
  Repository (T3.5) layers cross-Conn cache on top.
- Synchronous inbound RFC server (T2.7): Server type with
  Register / Start / Stop / Running. SetServerImpl wires
  the cgo backend's RfcRegisterServer +
  RfcInstallGenericServerFunction. Returns
  *UnsupportedFeatureError when no impl is installed
  (no-SDK build).
- Auth-set extensions (T2.8): SSO ticket (MYSAPSSO2),
  X.509, SAML 2.0 / Bearer params surfaced through
  `nwrfc.Params`. Cgo Open path forwards them via the
  generic param map.
- Connection event listeners (T2.9): ConnEvent enum
  (Opened / Closed / Broken) + Listener interface +
  ListenerFunc adapter. Add / Remove / fireEvent
  thread-safe. nwrfc.Open / Close fire automatically.

## v0.1.0 — 2026-05-07 (Tier 0 + Tier 1: production-grade synchronous client)

### Added — Tier 0 (security remediation)

- Removed legacy `gorfc/sapnwrfc.ini` containing real-looking SAP
  credentials and corporate hostnames in `*.wdf.sap.corp`.
- Replaced hardcoded credentials in `gorfc/gorfc_test.go` and
  `example/hello_gorfc.go` with `GORFC_TEST_*` env-var lookups; the
  legacy integration tests are now opt-in.
- New `.gitignore` patterns: `sapnwrfc.ini`, `**/sapnwrfc.ini`,
  `*.pse`, `**/sec/`, `nwrfcsdk/`, `sapcrypto/`.
- New `gorfc/sapnwrfc.ini.example` placeholder profile.
- New `docs/SECURITY.md` v0.
- New `.github/workflows/secret-scan.yml` running gitleaks.
- Tightened `gorfc/gorfc.go` build tag.
- Fixed `defer C.free` capture-before-assignment leak.
- New `docs/FEATURE_MATRIX.md`, `docs/SDK_FUNCTIONS_MAP.md`,
  `docs/ROADMAP.md`.

### Added — Tier 1 (core revival)

- New module path `github.com/cjordaoc/gorfc`. go.mod bumped
  to `go 1.23 + toolchain go1.25.0`. testify v1.10.0.
- New internal/backend, internal/sdkbackend (cgo SAP NWRFC
  SDK), internal/nosdkbackend, internal/ucs2,
  internal/timeext, internal/bcd packages.
- New public nwrfc package: Conn, Pool, Session, Params,
  CallOptions, Call, CallMap, EnsureSDK, SDKVersion,
  Capabilities, the 16-type error hierarchy, the four
  capability-extension wrappers (trace / lang / crypto /
  ini-reload).
- New documentation: docs/INSTALL.md, docs/BUILD.md,
  docs/CONFIGURATION.md, docs/ERRORS.md.

### Changed — breaking from upstream `github.com/sap/gorfc`

- Module path migration.
- Date/time policy: ABAP "00000000"/"000000" no longer
  silently maps to zero `time.Time`.
- Error shape: 16 typed structs + sentinels.

### Fixed

- Memory leak in legacy `fillVariable`.
- Build tag falsely allowed compile on any amd64 GOOS.
- Committed credentials.

### Security

- See docs/SECURITY.md §8 for the historical exposure note.

## Pre-revival (upstream history)

0.2.0 (2020-06-09)
- ABAP datatypes support completed (RFC_DECF16, RFC_DECF34, RFC_UTCLONG).
- Error handling extended with GoRfc error type.
- RFCTYPE_XSTRING wrap fix.
- ABAP input parameters check extended.

0.1.0 (2020-05-04)
- Darwin support.
- New connection parameters added, type changed to map.
- New connection attributes added, type changed to map.
- Table parameter accepts also array of variables.
- ABAP datatypes conversions fixed.
- ABAP INT8 type added.

0.0.1 (2016-02-01)
- Initial release.
